  "summary": "The 6-Month Treasury Bill rate (DTB6) has been in a remarkably stable regime since December 2025, oscillating around a mean of 3.508% with daily std of only 0.019%. The last observed value is 3.53% (Feb 26). With no FOMC meeting before the March 12 resolution (next is March 18-19) and Fed futures showing no rate change expected through April, the rate should remain near current levels. An Ornstein-Uhlenbeck mean-reversion simulation over 10 business days pulls the distribution center slightly below 3.53 toward the regime mean (~3.516). Three independent Monte Carlo models (Gaussian OU, t-distributed OU, and blended with jump risk) all converge on consistent percentiles. The distribution is tight reflecting the exceptional regime stability.",
